SYSCO Corp. of Houston said it issued $330 million face value of zero-coupon, subordinated notes due October 2004 at $397.27 per $1,000 face amount, or a yield to maturity of 6.25%. 

The food service concern said the notes are convertible into 12.256 shares of Sysco per $1,000 face amount.
Sysco said that proceeds from the liquid yield option notes of approximately $130 million will be used to reduce outstanding commercial paper and reduce the company's revolving loan.
Merrill Lynch Capital Markets was the underwriter. 

